  "title": "Project manager (Cheque clearing)",
  "description": "<p>We are looking for experienced professionals to support a project related to Singapore cheque clearing for SGD and USD. The ideal candidates must have hands-on domain knowledge and prior experience in Singapore’s cheque clearing processes, systems, and regulatory requirements.</p><p>Both roles require strong understanding of the operational and technical workflows involved in cheque clearing within the Singapore banking ecosystem.</p><p></p><p>1. Project Manager (PM)</p><p>Key Responsibilities:</p><p>•Lead and manage end-to-end delivery of the Singapore cheque clearing project (SGD & USD).</p><p>•Coordinate with internal teams, external vendors, and stakeholders.</p><p>•Develop project plans, timelines, and progress reports.</p><p>•Identify project risks and drive mitigation strategies.</p><p>•Ensure compliance with MAS and local clearing regulations.</p><p>•Facilitate project meetings and document key decisions.</p><p>•Oversee user acceptance testing (UAT) and implementation activities.</p><p>Required Skills & Experience:</p><p>•Proven experience as a Project Manager in banking or financial services.</p><p>•Mandatory: Prior experience in Singapore cheque clearing domain.</p><p>•Strong understanding of cheque clearing workflows, systems, and regulations.</p><p>•Excellent communication, stakeholder management, and documentation skills.</p><p>Ability to manage cross-functional teams and drive on-time delivery</p><p></p><p></p>",
